You seem like a good mannered type of person so I will explain further since you really want to know.You say you have to have an attack with each counter attack.

That is partly true, but I did say counter- attack, which means counter the attack. You do not always have to counter-attack using an attack. You can counter the attack that was forced upon you using other methods. Attacking would be only the last method. If you are a wise person like I am and would rather counter the attack instead of using force to try and survive then you are missing the whole picture of pvp. You want to win the fight. This does not mean that you have to kill your opponent or use force. A thief can win without fighting for example, but this is a drastic part of the spectrum. If you do not die then you will win the fight. 

Please consider this site which may help you to understand my line of reason. The last portion of  shows the true meaning of counter- attacking.http://www.lwcbooks.com/articles/edgedweapons.html


Thank you for being reasonable and asking questions like a good student.

